">cordless phones</a> available. The cordless phone system comes with two handsets, but you can add up to a dozen. With so many handsets, it doesn&#39;t matter how many rooms you have or how many cubicles you need to fit with cordless phones, you have the ability to add the handsets you need.","The battery life for these phones clocks in at seven hours of talking time. If you don&#39;t talk on the phone too frequently, you will get about seven days of battery life when the phone is in standby mode. This home phone has an answering machine that stores 14 minutes of messages. However, the base doesn&#39;t offer a speakerphone. Fortunately, there is a speakerphone on the individual handsets, but it would be nice if you could use the base as a speakerphone, too.","The handsets have caller ID and support conference calls. You won&#39;t be able to set an alarm with these phones, but you can pair your cell phone via Bluetooth or use a wireless headset easily. The phone doesn&#39;t support text messaging forwarding, though.","One extremely helpful feature is the intercom. Since you can expand the set to 12 handsets, you will be able to reach different members of your family even if they are all the way across the house in different rooms or behind closed doors.","This cordless house phone stores 100 entries in its phonebook and will remember the last 50 callers. It also stores the past five numbers you dialed. You can enable a silent setting for different handsets when you want a specific room to be quiet but still want to receive phone calls in other areas like the kitchen or living room.","You get a one-year warranty with Uniden&#39;s D1780-BT cordless phone set. Uniden has great customer support, and you can reach representatives by phone or email. The company doesn&#39;t offer live chat online, but you can read a FAQs page on the website or download a full version of the instruction manual if you need to."]},"id":"4d0b7115-1b4e-4dd1-a3bb-d7ecaa329a4c","type":"text"},{"d